if the Chinese can obtain new technology from corporate espionage.

182
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:42,850
弗兰克  你觉得呢
Frank, what do you think?

183
00:09:42,850 --> 00:09:44,670
我更倾向于雷蒙德的想法
I lean more toward Raymond's thinking.

184
00:09:44,670 --> 00:09:47,950
如果引起中方的反感  那多年的努力都白费了
If we antagonize the Chinese we could undo years of progress.

185
00:09:47,950 --> 00:09:51,030
我可以低调行事  绝不会使强硬手腕
Allow me to do this quietly, with a soft touch.

186
00:09:51,030 --> 00:09:52,780
我不会激怒他们  先生
I won't antagonize them, sir.

187
00:09:52,780 --> 00:09:55,140
我们最要不得的就是自找麻烦
The last thing we want to do is rock the boat.

188
00:09:55,140 --> 00:09:56,440
你想怎么办  凯瑟琳
What do you have in mind, Catherine?

189
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:58,270
建议性议程
A suggested agenda.

190
00:09:58,760 --> 00:09:59,980
而不是作为要求
Not a demand.

191
00:09:59,980 --> 00:10:03,020
这件事由中层出面  我根本不插手
We'll keep it mid-level. I won't get anywhere near it.

192
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:04,710
雷蒙德
Raymond?

193
00:10:05,490 --> 00:10:07,310
我已经表明了顾虑
I've voiced my concerns.

194
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:14,530
-要格外谨慎克制  -我向您保证  先生
- A very soft touch. - You have my word, sir.

195
00:10:15,110 --> 00:10:15,870
好
Good.

196
00:10:17,900 --> 00:10:20,640
雷蒙德  一起吃个午餐吧
Raymond? Want to grab some lunch?

197
00:10:22,560 --> 00:10:23,830
乐意之极
Would love to.

198
00:10:23,990 --> 00:10:26,380
谢谢  弗兰克  欢迎加入白宫
Thanks, Frank. Welcome to the West Wing.

199
00:10:26,380 --> 00:10:27,660
谢谢您  先生
Thank you, sir.

200
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:38,050
总统就像旷野上的一棵孤树
The president is like a lone tree in an empty field.

201
00:10:38,050 --> 00:10:40,120
风往哪吹  他就往哪倒
He leans whichever way the wind is blowing.

202
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:44,350
现在雷蒙德·塔斯克的西风吹得实在太猛
And right now Raymond Tusk blows far too strong from the west.

203
00:10:44,740 --> 00:10:46,180
那是假发吗
Is that a wig?

204
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:50,260
不是  他都留了好几个月了
No. He's been growing it out for months.

205
00:10:50,700 --> 00:10:53,030
戴安说她喜欢长发
Diane says she likes it long.

206
00:10:53,030 --> 00:10:55,290
我告诉她  等她看到
I told her she'll feel differently

207
00:10:55,290 --> 00:10:57,610
他留起长发辩就会改主意了
once she sees the first dread lock.

208
00:10:57,620 --> 00:10:59,660
或者闻到
Or smells it.

209
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:05,510
我上周末去看了你女儿
I went to see your daughter last weekend.

210
00:11:08,090 --> 00:11:09,090
她怎么样
How is she?

211
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:11,390
-想看看照片吗  -好啊
- You want to see a picture? - Okay.

212
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:16,320
-她妈妈在吗  -嗯
- Was her mother there? - Yeah.

213
00:11:17,850 --> 00:11:19,140
他们的钱够用吧
Are they okay on money?

214
00:11:19,140 --> 00:11:21,940
格林伍兹的保险率费一月份要上调了
The rate at Greenwoods is going up in January.

215
00:11:21,940 --> 00:11:24,060
凯特琳娜担心钱不够用
Catalina is worried she's gonna be short.

216
00:11:24,910 --> 00:11:27,170
我会多打点去她账上
I'll make sure to put more into the account.

217
00:11:27,180 --> 00:11:29,120
如果你不舒服  我们不用聊她
We don't have to talk about her if you don't...

218
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:32,900
不不  没事  我很感谢你去看她
No, no, no. It's fine. I appreciate you going to see her.

219
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:33,670
抱歉  泰德
I'm sorry, Ted.

220
00:11:33,670 --> 00:11:35,850
你邀我一起吃午餐  我以为你是想...
I thought that when you asked me to lunch it was because you want --

221
00:11:35,850 --> 00:11:39,270
不不  没错
No, no, no. I mean, yes,

222
00:11:39,280 --> 00:11:41,940
我想确保她们的需求都得到满足
I want to make sure they have what they need.

223
00:11:41,990 --> 00:11:43,010
但是  不
But, no,

224
00:11:43,820 --> 00:11:47,450
我想找你谈是为了...
the reason I wanted to talk --

225
00:11:49,630 --> 00:11:50,930
洛莉·塔特
Lorrie Tate.

226
00:11:50,990 --> 00:11:53,640
洛莉是我朋友  她怎么了
Lorrie's a friend of mine. What about her?

227
00:11:55,020 --> 00:11:58,100
她说你有意竞选党鞭
She mentioned you're interested in the whip's race.

228
00:11:58,100 --> 00:11:59,320
天呐
Oh, no.

229
00:12:01,230 --> 00:12:02,700
真希望她没这么说
I wish she hadn't.

230
00:12:02,780 --> 00:12:03,940
为什么
Why not?

231
00:12:03,940 --> 00:12:06,250
因为很荒唐啊
Because it's ridiculous.

232
00:12:06,510 --> 00:12:07,470
是吗
Is it?

233
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:12,680
我只是随口说说
I just mentioned it off-hand.

234
00:12:13,210 --> 00:12:15,720
韦伯和巴克沃特的竞争简直...
The whole Webb and Buchwalter thing is just --

235
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:17,020
一团糟
Complete mess.

236
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:18,620
但我是开玩笑的
But I wasn't serious.

237
00:12:18,620 --> 00:12:20,490
我觉得你该认真想想
I think you should be serious.

238
00:12:20,850 --> 00:12:21,890
你想竞选党鞭吗
Do you want to do it?

239
00:12:21,900 --> 00:12:24,430
我没有经验啊  泰德  我还...
I don't have the experience, Ted. And I -- I --

240
00:12:24,430 --> 00:12:25,130
想不想
Yes or no?

241
00:12:25,140 --> 00:12:26,990
当然想
Yes, of course.

242
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:28,320
将来再说
Someday.

243
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:31,190
但现在  我没有他们那样的财力
But now I -- I don't have the money they do.

244
00:12:31,190 --> 00:12:32,920
你用我的钱  就有了
Unless you use mine.

245
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:34,820
你不能把你的钱浪费在...
You can't waste your money on --

246
00:12:34,820 --> 00:12:37,050
如果我找到那些还持观望态度的人
If I funnel my PAC money

247
00:12:37,050 --> 00:12:38,580
把我的政治行动委员会资金给他们一些
to some folks who are on the fence,

248
00:12:38,580 --> 00:12:42,380
在你正式宣布前  拉拢一些支持者
round up a couple dozen commitments before you announce,

249
00:12:42,380 --> 00:12:45,560
那你立刻就是有力竞争者
that would make you an instant contender.

250
00:12:45,560 --> 00:12:47,110
你说这是浪费吗
Now tell me that's a waste.

251
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:48,910
这可是几十万啊
We're talking hundreds of thousands.

252
00:12:48,910 --> 00:12:51,660
这可不是圣诞礼物  杰姬
It's not a Christmas present, Jackie.

253
00:12:51,660 --> 00:12:54,600
如果你是党鞭  我就在领导层有了坚定的盟友
With you as whip I have a strong ally in the leadership.

254
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:56,960
我的获益不比你少
I stand to gain as much as you.

255
00:12:58,510 --> 00:12:59,720
稍等片刻
Hang on one second.

256
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:01,860
我不知道哪里...
I don't know where the...

257
00:13:05,210 --> 00:13:06,980
怎么样  他信了吗
How did it go? Did he buy it?

258
00:13:07,020 --> 00:13:10,020
不管你给他吹了什么风  吹得很到位
Whatever bug you put in his ear burrowed deep.

259
00:13:10,070 --> 00:13:12,810
很简单  他喜欢你  对你视如己出
It was easy. The man adores you like you're his own child.

260
00:13:12,810 --> 00:13:15,080
但你可得选我做首席副党鞭
But you sure as hell better make me Chief Deputy.

261
00:13:15,570 --> 00:13:17,130
我得先当选
I need to win first.

262
00:13:17,210 --> 00:13:19,490
我和泰德两票  还剩111票
Ted and I make two. 111 to go.

263
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:22,610
副党鞭会数数总是好事
It's always good when the Chief Deputy knows her arithmetic.

264
00:13:22,610 --> 00:13:24,700
别扯淡  我们数票吧
Fuck off. Let's start taking names.

265
00:13:25,620 --> 00:13:27,080
这个还不错
This one seems promising.

266
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:31,080
康纳·埃利斯  可靠  有经验
Connor Ellis. He's solid. Good experience.

267
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:33,300
是他解决了琼斯参议员
Oh, he's the one that got Senator Jones out of that mess

268
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:34,380
{\an8}借调查名义影响民意的民意调查

269
00:13:33,300 --> 00:13:34,380
推手民调的烂摊子
with the push polling.

270
00:13:34,380 --> 00:13:36,910
是啊  免受纪律委员会的调查
Yes. Kept him from the ethics committee.

271
00:13:37,150 --> 00:13:38,440
面试一下吧
Let's set up an interview.

272
00:13:38,770 --> 00:13:40,290
我安排一下日程
I'll find a good time in schedule.

273
00:13:41,010 --> 00:13:43,130
我们说说日程的事
Let's talk about the schedule.

274
00:13:43,130 --> 00:13:47,320
好好挑一下我该参加哪些活动
I think we need to be more selective with the events I do.

275
00:13:47,590 --> 00:13:49,580
有些是上任副总统夫人没去成的
Some of these are leftovers from Mrs. Matthews.

276
00:13:49,580 --> 00:13:51,520
你想取消也可以
We can cancel whatever you like.

277
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:53,680
这是什么
And what's this?

278
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:57,750
你丈夫要为两位新晋海军陆战队将军授衔
Your husband will be pinning stars on two newly commissioned Marine generals.

279
00:13:57,750 --> 00:13:59,080
这个你应该去
I think that's one you should do.

280
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:00,530
给我介绍一下
Okay. Walk me through it.

281
00:14:00,820 --> 00:14:02,960
两位将军分别是艾莉西娅·汉普顿
The generals are Alicia Hampton

282
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:04,670
和道顿·麦金尼斯
and Dalton McGinnis.

283
00:14:04,720 --> 00:14:06,250
6点50到场
Arriving at 6:50 --

284
00:14:06,250 --> 00:14:07,530
道顿·麦金尼斯吗
Dalton McGinnis?

285
00:14:07,630 --> 00:14:09,550
是的  认识吗
Yes. Do you know him?

286
00:14:14,300 --> 00:14:15,800
大学同学
We went to college together.

287
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:18,970
刚说到哪了
I'm sorry, where were we?

288
00:14:19,620 --> 00:14:20,700
什么时候到
Arrive what time?

289
00:14:20,710 --> 00:14:21,730
6点50
6:50.

290
00:14:21,770 --> 00:14:24,370
很好  出席人员名单给我一份
Great. I'd like a list of all the people that will be attending.

291
00:14:25,030 --> 00:14:27,340
我被排除在外没什么
It's not that big a deal if I get left out,

292
00:14:27,350 --> 00:14:29,260
可你是国务卿啊
but you're the secretary of state.

293
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:31,830
塔斯克怎么能参与决策
I mean, Tusk should not be determining policy.

294
00:14:31,830 --> 00:14:35,530
只有总统可以决定你该怎么做
The president alone should instruct you on what you are to pursue.

295
00:14:35,540 --> 00:14:37,140
他们什么关系
What's their relationship?

296
00:14:37,140 --> 00:14:38,820
他一直给总统出谋划策
He's had his ear for years.

297
00:14:38,820 --> 00:14:40,060
那是顾问
An advisor...

298
00:14:40,060 --> 00:14:43,150
更像是导师  总统很重视他的建议
More of a mentor. And one whose advice is not easily dismissed.

299
00:14:43,150 --> 00:14:45,240
他还会继续要求忽视网络战
He's gonna keep pushing back on cyber warfare.

300
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:46,520
除非我给提上议程
Not if I get it on the agenda.

301
00:14:46,520 --> 00:14:48,900
不  你提上议程他更会来劲
No, especially if you get it on the agenda.

302
00:14:49,630 --> 00:14:51,090
商贸联委会谈判再度开启时
Tusk is not gonna take any chances

303
00:14:51,090 --> 00:14:53,970
塔斯克绝不会冒丝毫风险
when the next Joint Commission talks come around.

304
00:14:53,970 --> 00:14:55,810
你刚刚不是支持他吗
You agreed with him in the meeting.

305
00:14:55,810 --> 00:14:58,670
如果我们站一边  他的态度只会更强硬
If we had ganged up, he would have taken a firmer position.

306
00:14:58,670 --> 00:14:59,550
说不定
For all we know,

307
00:14:59,550 --> 00:15:02,710
他现在就在劝总统改主意呢
he's convincing the president right now to change his mind.

308
00:15:02,710 --> 00:15:06,040
所以我们绝不能给他机会
Now we need to remove that option as a possibility.

309
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:07,590
怎么办
How?

310
00:15:09,230 --> 00:15:13,250
这次谈判中就强迫中方回应网络安全问题
Force the Chinese to confront the issue now, this round of talks.

311
00:15:13,260 --> 00:15:15,210
我答应总统不采取强硬手段的
I promised the president a soft touch.

312
00:15:15,210 --> 00:15:17,700
我不能有意食言
I can't intentionally break my promise.

313
00:15:18,060 --> 00:15:19,910
如果是无意的呢
What if it was unintentional?

314
00:15:22,520 --> 00:15:25,220
凯茜  如果你不喜欢现在的局势
Cathy, if you don't like how the table is set,

315
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:26,830
就干脆搅局
turn over the table.

316
00:15:31,880 --> 00:15:32,960
你偷吸
You're cheating.

317
00:15:33,210 --> 00:15:35,200
哪有  是电子烟
No, I'm not. It's vapor.

318
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:36,310
那也算
Still.

319
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:38,030
你该试试
You should try it.

320
00:15:38,410 --> 00:15:40,690
会上瘾  但没副作用
Addiction without the consequences.

321
00:15:40,700 --> 00:15:42,050
你自己抽
It's all yours.

322
00:15:43,340 --> 00:15:44,530
不睡吗
You staying up?

323
00:15:46,560 --> 00:15:48,670
明晚的授衔仪式
This ceremony tomorrow night.

324
00:15:48,680 --> 00:15:50,040
你不想去
You don't want to go.

325
00:15:50,040 --> 00:15:51,670
除非我必须去
If I don't have to.

326
00:15:51,680 --> 00:15:53,440
我也不喜欢
I hate these sorta things, too.

327
00:15:53,450 --> 00:15:56,710
但这是副总统的首次亮相
But it is my first public appearance as vice president.

328
00:15:59,380 --> 00:16:00,280
好吧
Okay.

329
00:16:00,290 --> 00:16:01,380
谢谢
Thank you.

330
00:16:06,470 --> 00:16:09,630
要不要把这儿改成办公室
Should we turn this into a proper office?

331
00:16:09,870 --> 00:16:13,560
可以啊  楼下没有私密性
That's not a bad idea. No privacy downstairs.

332
00:16:14,340 --> 00:16:16,050
我去找装修队
I'll talk to the contractor.

333
00:16:17,030 --> 00:16:18,260
晚安  弗兰西斯
Goodnight, Francis.

334
00:16:18,270 --> 00:16:19,380
晚安
Goodnight.

335
00:16:41,610 --> 00:16:43,270
先生  先生  根据国会议事录
Sir! Sir! Congressional Record.

336
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:45,090
不是要谈到六点吗
Weren't the talks supposed to go until six?

337
00:16:45,090 --> 00:16:46,530
他们不听  我们谈不下去
We can't talk if they won't listen.

338
00:16:46,530 --> 00:16:47,910
中方不谈了吗
Did the Chinese walk out?

339
00:16:47,910 --> 00:16:49,940
我们已经表明  除非他们肯谈政府资助的
We made it clear that we won't discuss any other issues

340
00:16:49,940 --> 00:16:52,600
网络攻击  否则其他问题免谈
until government-sponsored cyber attacks are on the table.

341
00:16:52,810 --> 00:16:54,240
显然他们不开心了
Apparently that's not what they wanted to hear.

342
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:56,960
中方代表离席之前你说了什么
Sir, what did you tell the Chinese delegation before they walked out?

343
00:16:56,960 --> 00:16:58,210
我们没派人去
We didn't have anybody there.

344
00:16:58,210 --> 00:17:00,440
商贸联委会谈判通常很无聊的
The Joint Commission is usually a snooze-fest.

345
00:17:00,440 --> 00:17:01,680
今天不是
Not today it wasn't.

346
00:17:01,680 --> 00:17:02,890
我已经让格里尔去弄了
I've got Greer on it.

347
00:17:02,890 --> 00:17:04,260
这不是国际板块的新闻吗
Isn't this international?

348
00:17:04,700 --> 00:17:05,810
如果要写网络战的背景资料
We need somebody from the tech beat

349
00:17:05,810 --> 00:17:08,300
就得请科技板块的记者
if we want any background on cyber warfare.

350
00:17:08,330 --> 00:17:09,860
他找到人接受署名采访了吗
Does he have anybody on record yet?

351
00:17:09,860 --> 00:17:10,750
中方不肯谈
The Chinese aren't talking.

352
00:17:10,750 --> 00:17:13,210
美国代表团的话美联社都报道了
And all the U.S. delegation said is what's in the AP wire.

353
00:17:13,210 --> 00:17:15,290
无论如何两小时内网上要出报道
I want something online in the next two hours.

354
00:17:15,380 --> 00:17:17,400
本周内发一篇深入后续报道
In-depth follow-up sometime this week.

355
00:17:19,600 --> 00:17:20,520
卢卡斯
Hey, Lucas?

356
00:17:22,690 --> 00:17:23,880
你还好吗
You all right?

357
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:26,550
好啊  怎么了
Yeah. Why?

358
00:17:27,270 --> 00:17:29,550
你还穿着昨天穿的那身
You're wearing the same clothes you wore yesterday.

359
00:17:31,290 --> 00:17:32,120
是吗
Am I?

360
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:35,240
我不知道你私生活发生了什么
I don't know what's going on in your personal life,

361
00:17:35,750 --> 00:17:37,630
但似乎已经影响到你的工作了
but it seems to be entering the workplace.

362
00:17:37,630 --> 00:17:38,810
仪表很重要
Appearances matter.

