00:17:38,810 --> 00:17:40,640
我们的编辑不能比他的记者
And we can't have an editor looking more disheveled

364
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:41,850
还不修边幅
than his reporters.

365
00:17:42,870 --> 00:17:45,210
两小时  一定给你个交待
Two hours. You'll have something.

366
00:17:45,770 --> 00:17:48,060
你知道杰姬·夏普要竞选党鞭吗
Did you know Jackie Sharp's running for Whip?

367
00:17:48,060 --> 00:17:49,680
不知道  这是我第一次听说
No, this is the first I'm hearing of it.

368
00:17:49,680 --> 00:17:50,940
我跟韦伯说了
I spoke to Webb.

369
00:17:50,940 --> 00:17:52,750
洛莉·塔特给他发了一封关于我的电邮
He got an email from Lorrie Tate about me.

370
00:17:52,750 --> 00:17:54,760
戴夫·霍兰德给我发了一封关于他的电邮
I got one from Dave Holland about him.

371
00:17:54,770 --> 00:17:56,010
这我不管
Which means nothing to me.

372
00:17:56,010 --> 00:17:59,700
公费旅游  任人唯亲  塔特跟夏普很亲密
The junkets, the nepotism. Tate and Sharp are close.

373
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:01,630
霍兰德跟她在退伍军人事务委员会共事过
Holland serves on the VA committee with her.

374
00:18:01,630 --> 00:18:03,310
她找别人出手  好撇清干系
She used proxies to insulate herself.

375
00:18:03,310 --> 00:18:05,640
你觉得是她把料爆给了他们
So you think that she gave the dirt to them.

376
00:18:05,640 --> 00:18:06,960
没错  她在耍我们两个人
Yeah. She's been playing both of us.

377
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:08,750
你觉得她能拉到多少支持者
How many commitments do you think she could have?

378
00:18:08,750 --> 00:18:09,920
目前也就20个左右吧
Around 20 so far.

379
00:18:09,920 --> 00:18:11,440
那她还是被你俩远远甩在后面啊
So she's a distant third.

380
00:18:11,440 --> 00:18:13,780
但她在一个个动摇我们的支持者啊
But she's picking people off us left and right.

381
00:18:13,780 --> 00:18:14,330
你得帮我
I want your help.

382
00:18:14,330 --> 00:18:16,180
我支持你啊  韦斯
You have my support, Wes.

383
00:18:16,190 --> 00:18:17,570
那就公开表态
Then make that public.

384
00:18:17,580 --> 00:18:20,180
如果我公开支持你  博奇就会支持韦伯
If I come out for you, Birch comes out for Webb.

385
00:18:20,180 --> 00:18:21,740
那反倒会害你  而不是帮你
That's gonna hurt you, not help you.

386
00:18:21,740 --> 00:18:23,190
情况很不妙  弗兰克
This is serious, Frank.

387
00:18:23,190 --> 00:18:24,930
泰德·哈维梅耶在赞助她
Ted Havemeyer is bankrolling her.

388
00:18:24,930 --> 00:18:26,540
你想过跟杰姬谈谈吗
Have you thought of talking to Jackie?

389
00:18:26,540 --> 00:18:29,290
没有  原则上我不能那么做
No, no. I can't do that on principle.

390
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:30,090
为什么不行
Why not?

391
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:33,040
我不会跟哈维梅耶支持的人合作
Anyone who Havemeyer is backing, I don't work with.

392
00:18:33,040 --> 00:18:35,260
我竞选参议员的时候  他也搅了我的局
He pulled the same crap on me when I ran for Senate.

393
00:18:35,260 --> 00:18:37,960
他赞助我的主要对手  混蛋
He financed my primary opponent. Asshole.

394
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:39,120
那由你决定
Well, that is your call.

395
00:18:39,120 --> 00:18:41,250
但如果你要让旧账阻碍你的竞选
But if you're gonna let an old grudge get in the way of progress --

396
00:18:41,250 --> 00:18:42,780
我就是不能这么做  弗兰克
I just can't do it, Frank.

397
00:18:42,780 --> 00:18:45,800
哈维梅耶这些年一直想把我赶下去
Havemeyer's been trying to shove me down the totem pole for years.

398
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:47,290
我不会让他得逞的
I won't give him the satisfaction.

399
00:18:47,290 --> 00:18:50,240
我尊重你  但这样我就无能为力了
Well, I can respect that, but my hands are tied.

400
00:18:51,110 --> 00:18:52,050
这件事很微妙
It's a delicate matter,

401
00:18:52,050 --> 00:18:54,600
但我们正在和中国政府沟通
but we are in communication with the Chinese government

402
00:18:54,610 --> 00:18:55,700
如何推进谈判
as to how to move forward.

403
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:57,500
那么美国将在网络攻击的事上屈服吗
Does this mean the U.S. will back down on cyber attacks?

404
00:18:57,500 --> 00:18:59,280
美国从不屈服
The United States never backs down,

405
00:18:59,290 --> 00:19:02,330
特别是在重要问题上
particularly on issues that are high priority to us.

406
00:19:02,330 --> 00:19:03,430
国务卿女士  您是怎么
Madam Secretary, what did you--

407
00:19:03,430 --> 00:19:04,220
谢谢
Thank you.

408
00:19:04,220 --> 00:19:06,160
您是怎么跟代表团团长说的
What did you tell the head of the delegation?

409
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:12,050
代表团越界了
The delegation overstepped its bounds,

410
00:19:12,050 --> 00:19:14,360
但凯茜不能坑她自己的人
but Cathy couldn't throw her own people under the bus.

411
00:19:14,360 --> 00:19:16,990
她公开发表言论前该先跟我们商量一下
She should have consulted us first before speaking publicly.

412
00:19:16,990 --> 00:19:18,270
媒体堵在她家门口
The press was on her doorstep

413
00:19:18,270 --> 00:19:19,730
总统又在地球另一端
and the president was in another hemisphere.

414
00:19:19,820 --> 00:19:21,740
我不是在批评她的做法
Now, look, I'm not condemning what she did,

415
00:19:21,820 --> 00:19:23,340
但她总得采取措施
but she had to do something.

416
00:19:23,340 --> 00:19:25,910
她凭直觉做决定  并采取了行动
She made a gut call and she acted.

417
00:19:25,910 --> 00:19:27,780
咱们得撇清关系
We have to distance ourselves from this.

418
00:19:27,780 --> 00:19:28,950
总统什么时候回来
When is the president back?

419
00:19:28,950 --> 00:19:29,670
明天早上
Tomorrow morning.

420
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:30,860
我们能安排一次会面吗
Can we set up a meeting?

421
00:19:30,860 --> 00:19:32,780
凯茜得公开道歉
Cathy needs to publicly apologize.

422
00:19:32,780 --> 00:19:34,480
我们能让她跟总统谈谈吗
Can we get her in the room with the president?

423
00:19:34,480 --> 00:19:36,800
我们不应该先统一一下步调吗
Shouldn't we all be on the same page first?

424
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:37,620
我再想想办法吧
I'll see what I can do.

425
00:19:37,620 --> 00:19:38,760
谢谢
Thank you.

426
00:19:38,770 --> 00:19:40,920
我去拿吃的之前  你问我了一个问题
Now, you asked me a question before I went and got my food.

427
00:19:40,920 --> 00:19:43,860
副总统先生  我是麦金尼斯将军
Mr. Vice President. General McGinnis.

428
00:19:43,860 --> 00:19:46,110
不胜荣幸  希望你不介意
it's a great honor. I hope you don't mind.

429
00:19:46,110 --> 00:19:48,330
总统也想出席  他让我代为参加
The president wishes he could be here. He's asked me to fill in.

430
00:19:48,330 --> 00:19:49,450
荣幸的是我  先生
The honor is mine, sir.

431
00:19:49,450 --> 00:19:51,270
将军  这是我妻子  克莱尔
And, General, this is my wife, Claire.

432
00:19:51,270 --> 00:19:54,730
很高兴见到你  克莱尔  好久不见
It's good to see you, Claire. It's been a long time.

433
00:19:54,730 --> 00:19:55,660
是啊
Yes.

434
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:57,340
哈佛的同学
Harvard. We were classmates.

435
00:19:57,340 --> 00:19:58,750
克莱尔没提过这事
Claire didn't say a thing.

436
00:19:58,760 --> 00:20:00,360
我们还约会过
We dated for a time.

437
00:20:01,350 --> 00:20:02,770
只有五分钟
About five minutes.

438
00:20:03,660 --> 00:20:05,400
好了  不打扰你们用餐了
Anyway, I'll let you get back to your meal.

439
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:07,690
谢谢  我想起来了
Thank you. I've remembered.

440
00:20:07,690 --> 00:20:08,750
有意思的是
Interestingly enough,

441
00:20:08,750 --> 00:20:12,050
南卡罗莱纳州第一大作物不是棉花
in South Carolina the largest crop is not cotton.

442
00:20:12,050 --> 00:20:13,970
而是烟草
No. It's tobacco.

443
00:20:14,140 --> 00:20:17,080
第三大作物是大麻
And the third-largest crop is marijuana.

444
00:20:17,080 --> 00:20:20,770
咱心里明白就好
Now -- we'll just keep that to ourselves.

445
00:20:20,990 --> 00:20:23,020
失陪一下
Would you all excuse me for just a moment?

446
00:20:24,420 --> 00:20:25,790
-只有她一个吗  -是的
- Is she alone? - Yes.

447
00:20:25,790 --> 00:20:27,580
我们想单独谈谈
Would you give us a few moments, please?

448
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:34,330
怎么了
What's wrong?

449
00:20:37,250 --> 00:20:38,310
是他
It was him.

450
00:20:39,870 --> 00:20:40,730
谁
Who?

451
00:20:42,990 --> 00:20:44,220
大一那年
Freshman year.

452
00:20:47,650 --> 00:20:52,190
那件事...是麦金尼斯吗
You mean... McGinnis?

453
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:58,400
弗兰西斯  弗兰西斯  别做傻事
Francis, Francis. Please, don't do anything.

454
00:20:58,400 --> 00:20:59,800
我绝不会给他授衔...
I am not gonna pin a medal on that --

455
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:00,660
你必须授衔
You have to.

456
00:21:00,660 --> 00:21:02,250
等一下  不能让他
Just a minute, please! There is no way that man --

457
00:21:02,250 --> 00:21:03,260
先生  典礼要开始了
Sir, they want to start the ceremony.

458
00:21:03,270 --> 00:21:05,180
等一会儿  他不配接受...
Just a minute, please! He does not deserve a medal..

459
00:21:05,180 --> 00:21:06,070
弗兰西斯  求你了
Francis. I beg of you.

460
00:21:06,070 --> 00:21:07,210
我告诉你  枪毙他都不过分
I'm telling you, that man deserves to be taken out and shot.

461
00:21:07,210 --> 00:21:08,250
我求你了
I am begging you.

462
00:21:08,250 --> 00:21:08,850
-不行  -求你了
- No. - Please!

463
00:21:08,850 --> 00:21:10,070
-不要  -别...
- No. - Do not --

464
00:21:10,070 --> 00:21:11,550
我说等等
I said just a minute!

465
00:21:11,550 --> 00:21:14,310
求你了  别惹事
Do not make a scene. Please.

466
00:21:46,100 --> 00:21:46,880
汤姆
Tom.

467
00:21:48,680 --> 00:21:50,200
谢谢你能来
Thanks for coming by.

468
00:21:54,470 --> 00:21:58,790
我走进来时  我以为会有一丝怀念
You know, I thought I would miss this place the moment I stepped inside.

469
00:22:00,570 --> 00:22:01,670
可是没有
But I don't.

470
00:22:05,440 --> 00:22:06,600
喝斯黛拉没问题吧
Hope you like Stella.

471
00:22:13,960 --> 00:22:14,880
干杯
Cheers.

472
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:15,810
干杯
Beers up.

473
00:22:23,870 --> 00:22:24,950
你怎么样
How are things?

474
00:22:27,230 --> 00:22:30,530
还不错  还不错
They're good. They're good.

475
00:22:33,740 --> 00:22:34,690
你开心吗
You're happy?

476
00:22:35,270 --> 00:22:37,150
我就没开心过
I haven't been happy a day in my life.

477
00:22:37,760 --> 00:22:39,020
不过现在有时间了
But I have time now.

478
00:22:39,240 --> 00:22:43,660
可以思考  写作  我最近在构思小说
To think. To write. Been working on a novel.

479
00:22:44,320 --> 00:22:45,140
是吗
Yeah?

480
00:22:46,190 --> 00:22:49,250
纯粹是狗屁  不过还凑合
It's absolute shit. That's okay.

481
00:22:49,800 --> 00:22:52,580
挺好的  汤姆  真挺好的
That's great, Tom. That's really great.

482
00:22:53,380 --> 00:22:54,600
有什么事
What's on your mind?

483
00:22:54,800 --> 00:22:56,750
找我来不是叙旧的吧
I know you didn't ask me here just to catch up.

484
00:23:12,330 --> 00:23:13,580
弗兰克·安德伍德
Frank Underwood.

485
00:23:14,260 --> 00:23:15,560
我万分荣幸地
On the president's behalf

486
00:23:15,560 --> 00:23:19,110
代表总统  授予艾莉西娅·汉普顿将军
it is my great honor to formerly recognize the selection

487
00:23:19,110 --> 00:23:22,050
美军欧洲司令部
of General Alicia Hampton as Commander,

488
00:23:22,050 --> 00:23:24,260
司令一职
United States European Command,

489
00:23:24,270 --> 00:23:25,910
授予道顿·麦金尼斯将军
and General Dalton McGinnis

490
00:23:25,910 --> 00:23:29,380
美国战略司令部司令一职
as Commander of the United States Strategic Command.

491
00:23:29,420 --> 00:23:32,010
两位模范领袖为美国海军陆战队
The United States Marine Corps has been well served

492
00:23:32,010 --> 00:23:36,720
做出了卓越贡献
by these two exemplary leaders.

493
00:23:36,740 --> 00:23:40,220
总统与我希望两位再接再厉
The president and I are grateful for their continued service.

494
00:23:50,170 --> 00:23:51,480
恭喜你
Congratulations.

495
00:23:51,490 --> 00:23:52,570
谢谢你  先生
Thank you, sir.

496
00:24:33,340 --> 00:24:34,620
你觉得我疯了吗
You think I'm insane?

497
00:24:35,980 --> 00:24:38,170
我不觉得你疯了
I don't think you're insane.

498
00:24:41,810 --> 00:24:43,700
只是经历了太多痛苦
I think you've been through a lot.

499
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:45,270
想探个究竟
Trying to make sense of it all.

500
00:24:45,270 --> 00:24:46,500
我知道我是对的
I know I'm right.

501
00:24:46,910 --> 00:24:48,650
那是自然
I'm sure I believe you are.

502
00:24:49,370 --> 00:24:51,590
酒驾的事的确是他掩盖的
It's a fact that he helped cover up the DUI.

503
00:24:51,590 --> 00:24:56,550
如果你手下的记者拿着这事来找你
Imagine if one of your reporters came to you with this story.

504
00:24:57,020 --> 00:24:57,960
你会登出去吗
Could you print a word of it?

505
00:24:57,960 --> 00:24:59,650
不会  但我会要求他们继续调查
No, but I'd have them keep digging.

506
00:24:59,650 --> 00:25:00,330
是吗
Would you?

507
00:25:00,330 --> 00:25:01,760
凭心而论
If you're honest with yourself,

508
00:25:01,760 --> 00:25:03,770
你不会说这故事太牵强了吗
wouldn't you tell them it seemed farfetched?

509
00:25:04,230 --> 00:25:05,280
笔记说明不了什么
Your notes aren't convincing.

510
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:07,580
警方报告也证实不了什么
The police reports don't prove a link.

511
00:25:08,040 --> 00:25:10,200
-还有你的妄加猜测  -我知道
- And the speculative leaps you're making... - I know.

512
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:13,390
律人要先律己
Hold yourself to the same standards as you hold your staff.

513
00:25:18,960 --> 00:25:20,610
你当时在和佐伊约会
You and Zoe were seeing each other.

514
00:25:21,930 --> 00:25:23,790
我是猜的  也许错了
I -- I'm assuming. Maybe I'm wrong.

515
00:25:28,740 --> 00:25:30,150
是在约会
We -- we were.

516
00:25:40,890 --> 00:25:43,230
第一任妻子去世时  我也接受不了
When I lost my first wife, it didn't add up.

517
00:25:44,110 --> 00:25:46,360
谁会在31岁就死于乳腺癌呢
Who dies of breast cancer at 31?

518
00:25:48,030 --> 00:25:52,570
我想起诉  告医生  医院  所有人
I wanted to sue. Doctors, the hospital, everyone.

519
00:25:53,090 --> 00:25:54,390
觉得他们在隐瞒什么
Thought they were hiding something.

520
00:25:56,800 --> 00:25:57,790
但没有
No.

521
00:25:59,170 --> 00:26:03,730
悲伤让人想要答案  但有时真的就没有
Grief demands an answer, but sometimes there isn't one.

522
00:26:05,300 --> 00:26:09,640
没人能挽救她  就是这样
Her life couldn't be saved. Period.

523
00:26:11,470 --> 00:26:12,870
我该怎么办
What do I do?

524
00:26:14,950 --> 00:26:16,800
你愿找人谈谈吗
Would you consider seeing someone?

525
00:26:17,420 --> 00:26:19,550
辛西娅去世时有个治疗师帮了我很多
There's a therapist who helped me a great deal when Cynthia passed away.

526
00:26:19,550 --> 00:26:20,150
我可以帮你联系...
I can put you in touch --

527
00:26:20,150 --> 00:26:21,950
不了  我不用见谁
No. I don't need to see somebody.

528
00:26:22,210 --> 00:26:23,260
卢卡斯
Lucas.

529
00:26:23,540 --> 00:26:26,020
很感谢你过来  汤姆
I appreciate you coming by, Tom.

530
00:26:27,650 --> 00:26:28,770
也谢谢你的啤酒
Thanks for the beer.

531
00:26:32,210 --> 00:26:33,470
随时联系我吧
You call me anytime.

532
00:26:42,190 --> 00:26:44,210
照顾好自己  卢卡斯
You take care of yourself, Lucas.

533
00:26:47,410 --> 00:26:48,410
我是认真的
I mean it.

534
00:27:01,580 --> 00:27:03,060
还打算去哪吗  先生
Any plans to go elsewhere, sir?

535
00:27:03,120 --> 00:27:05,180
不了  我们今晚不出去了  谢谢
No. We're in for the night. Thank you.

536
00:27:05,180 --> 00:27:05,830
好的  先生
Yes, sir.

537
00:27:17,460 --> 00:27:18,840
我累了
I'm tired.

538
00:28:08,870 --> 00:28:09,890
需要什么吗  先生
Do you need something, sir?

539
00:28:11,310 --> 00:28:14,990
我的遥控手柄  我想玩游戏
Uh, my remote. I want to play.

540
00:28:14,990 --> 00:28:16,300
就在这儿
It's right over here.

541
00:28:19,870 --> 00:28:20,990
谢谢
Thank you.

542
00:28:28,710 --> 00:28:30,730
网络出问题了吗  我上不了线
Is there something wrong with the Internet? I can't get online.

543
00:28:30,730 --> 00:28:32,160
我们封掉了连接
We had to disable the access.

544
00:28:32,160 --> 00:28:33,430
那个连接不安全
It's not a secure connection.

545
00:28:53,990 --> 00:28:55,880
能让我单独待会儿吗
Could you just give me a moment, please?

546
00:28:55,900 --> 00:28:58,160
只要您在外面  身边就得有人
Whenever you're out here, somebody needs to be with you.

547
00:28:59,840 --> 00:29:02,770
我在自家后院都不能独自待着吗
I can't be alone in my own backyard?

548
00:29:02,960 --> 00:29:06,210
我说了算倒可以  但我说了不算
If it were up to me, sir. But it's not up to me.

549
00:29:12,610 --> 00:29:14,180
好吧  密查姆
Okay, Meechum.

550
00:29:57,560 --> 00:29:59,760
你以为我不想摔东西吗
You think I don't want to smash things?

551
00:30:01,480 --> 00:30:04,630
我的愤怒是你无法想象的
I know what that anger is more than you can imagine.

552
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:10,410
他压着我的时候...
When he was on top of me --

553
00:30:10,410 --> 00:30:11,680
我们不需要说这个
We don't have to talk about it.

554
00:30:11,680 --> 00:30:13,190
不  我想说
No, I want to.

555
00:30:17,510 --> 00:30:20,250
他压着我的时候  我使劲推
When he was on top of me, I pressed my hand --

556
00:30:23,870 --> 00:30:27,610
用尽全力推他的脸
with everything I could I pressed it into his face.

557
00:30:29,420 --> 00:30:32,270
我使足了劲  弄伤了他的鼻子
I pressed it so hard I broke his nose.

558
00:30:33,810 --> 00:30:35,530
但那没能阻止他
That didn't stop him.

559
00:30:38,680 --> 00:30:40,480
他把床单塞进我嘴里
He shoved the sheets in my mouth.

560
00:30:40,480 --> 00:30:42,170
我几乎无法呼吸
I could barely breathe.

561
00:30:49,400 --> 00:30:51,910
每次我想起那个女孩
Every time I think of her

562
00:30:52,510 --> 00:30:54,220
被人那样按倒
pinned down like that

563
00:30:54,670 --> 00:30:56,630
我都会勒死她  弗朗西斯
I strangle her, Francis,

564
00:30:57,890 --> 00:30:59,860
这样她才不会勒死我
so she doesn't strangle me.

565
00:31:02,480 --> 00:31:06,190
我必须那样  我们必须那样
I have to. We have to.

566
00:31:09,820 --> 00:31:11,480
否则...
The alternative is --

567
00:31:13,560 --> 00:31:14,850
我无法忍受
it's unlivable.

568
00:31:20,800 --> 00:31:22,390
你该休息了
You should go to sleep.

569
00:31:26,950 --> 00:31:29,140
我不知道能不能睡着
I'm not sure if I can.

570
00:31:30,140 --> 00:31:32,600
那你就回楼下去
Then you should go back downstairs.

571
00:31:49,610 --> 00:31:51,910
早晨的时候  恨意也不会消退
You'll still feel the hate in the morning.

572
00:31:53,700 --> 00:31:57,590
你会利用那份恨意  但不是去报复他
You'll use that. But not on him.

573
00:32:10,430 --> 00:32:12,390
你到底说了什么
What did you communicate, exactly?

574
00:32:12,390 --> 00:32:14,020
我让他提起议事日程的事
I told him to bring up the agenda,

575
00:32:14,020 --> 00:32:17,110
指出战略对话的关键点  但别提要求
suggest bullet points for the SED, but make no demands.

576
00:32:17,110 --> 00:32:19,570
那怎么会被理解成最后通牒
And how did that translate into a direct ultimatum?

577
00:32:20,380 --> 00:32:23,740
有时我的代表会探究言外之意
Well, sometimes my delegates try to read between the lines.

578
00:32:23,740 --> 00:32:27,490
他们知道我为外交目的需要合理推卸责任
They know that I need plausible deniability for diplomatic purposes.

579
00:32:27,490 --> 00:32:28,900
那你为什么没有立刻否认
Why didn't you immediately recant?

580
00:32:28,900 --> 00:32:30,660
就我跟中国人打交道的经验看
In my experience with the Chinese,

581
00:32:30,660 --> 00:32:32,260
变卦会让他们觉得我们软弱
backpedaling makes us look weak.

582
00:32:32,260 --> 00:32:35,910
我当时有两个选择  丢脸或展示实力
I had two choices: Lose face or exhibit strength.

583
00:32:36,270 --> 00:32:37,540
我选择了后者
I chose the latter.

584
00:32:38,190 --> 00:32:39,550
好吧  凯瑟琳  我会很快跟你联系
All right, Catherine. I'll be in touch shortly.

585
00:32:39,550 --> 00:32:40,500
谢谢  先生
Thank you, sir.

586
00:32:49,850 --> 00:32:51,320
用我的私人线路打给雷蒙德
Get me Raymond on the private line.

587
00:32:56,130 --> 00:32:57,390
你觉得她是故意越界的吗
Do you think she overstepped on purpose?

588
00:32:57,390 --> 00:33:00,220
凯茜绝不会违反你的指令  不会故意违反
Cathy would never disobey your orders. Not on purpose.

589
00:33:00,720 --> 00:33:02,340
雷蒙德  弗兰克在我这儿
Raymond, I've got Frank here.

590
00:33:02,340 --> 00:33:03,610
就我们三个吗
Just the three of us?

591
00:33:03,610 --> 00:33:06,200
就三个  早上好  雷蒙德
Just us three. Morning, Raymond.

592
00:33:06,600 --> 00:33:08,000
我在北京的联系人
My contacts in Beijing

593
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:10,540
跟我说商务部部长很激动
tell me the minister of commerce is in a tizzy.

594
00:33:10,850 --> 00:33:13,910
他想以此为借口重拳出击
Wants to use this as an excuse to start clenching fists.

595
00:33:13,910 --> 00:33:16,560
我要么拆凯茜的台  要么支持她
Well, either I turn my back on Cathy or I stand behind her.

596
00:33:16,560 --> 00:33:17,650
选前者
It's gotta be the former.

597
00:33:17,650 --> 00:33:18,610
我同意
I agree.

598
00:33:18,710 --> 00:33:19,880
如果您不道歉
If you don't apologize,

599
00:33:19,880 --> 00:33:22,570
那就不是小矛盾  而是大摩擦了
you go from ruffling feathers to plucking them.

600
00:33:22,570 --> 00:33:24,890
中国人绝不会忍气吞声  总统先生
And the Chinese won't stand for that, Mr. President.

601
00:33:24,890 --> 00:33:27,510
说是我跟内阁之间意思传达有错误如何
What about perceived miscommunication between me and my cabinet?

602
00:33:27,510 --> 00:33:30,350
总统先生  现在的目标是继续谈判
Mr. President, right now the goal is to resume the talks.

603
00:33:30,350 --> 00:33:31,950
就别担心他们是怎么想的了
I wouldn't worry about perceptions.

604
00:33:32,030 --> 00:33:34,350
弗兰克没错  我们得现实点
Frank is right. We need to be pragmatic.

605
00:33:34,370 --> 00:33:36,000
先别担心场面上的事
Worry about appearances later.

606
00:33:39,650 --> 00:33:41,760
行  我让凯瑟琳拟一份致歉信
All right. I'll have Catherine draft an apology.

607
00:33:41,770 --> 00:33:43,960
不  必须由您亲自写  总统先生
No, it has to come from you, Mr. President.

608
00:33:44,470 --> 00:33:45,860
道歉要有份量
If the apology is to mean anything,

609
00:33:45,870 --> 00:33:47,580
就得由白宫出面
it must come from the White House.

610
00:33:47,580 --> 00:33:50,110
这样的确应该更有成效
That is certainly the more likely to succeed.

611
00:33:53,560 --> 00:33:56,050
行  那我亲自写  谢谢  雷蒙德
Fine. I'll do it then. Thank you, Raymond.

612
00:33:56,050 --> 00:33:57,200
谢谢你  加勒特
Thank you, Garrett.

613
00:33:59,830 --> 00:34:03,340
你听到他仍然直呼总统的名字吗
Do you hear how he still uses the president's given name?

614
00:34:03,340 --> 00:34:07,180
而沃克也毫不在意他的失敬
And that Walker doesn't flinch at the lack of respect it implies.

615
00:34:10,800 --> 00:34:13,180
先生  恕我直言
Sir, forgive me if this isn't the case,

616
00:34:13,180 --> 00:34:15,520
您好像有点犹豫
but you seem a bit hesitant.

617
00:34:15,860 --> 00:34:16,560
为什么这么说
Why do you say that?

618
00:34:16,560 --> 00:34:19,000
关于公众看法的事  您所言极是
Well, you've raised a good point about public perception.

619
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:19,750
我不想让您觉得
I don't want you to think that

620
00:34:19,750 --> 00:34:22,520
我对您的担忧毫不在意
I'm dismissing your concerns casually.

621
00:34:22,520 --> 00:34:24,910
没有  你也担心这个吗
No. It's a concern for you, too?

622
00:34:25,160 --> 00:34:27,560
凯茜提出的观点不无道理
There is some insight into what Cathy brought up.

623
00:34:27,590 --> 00:34:29,160
变卦就是软弱
Backpedalling is weakness.

624
00:34:32,440 --> 00:34:34,990
跟中国人合作总是碰运气
Well, it's always a coin toss with the Chinese.

625
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:39,130
但有时候坚定立场比让步妥协要好
But sometimes standing your ground is better than giving in.

626
00:34:39,790 --> 00:34:43,160
你强势  他们反而更尊重你
They respect you more when you show strength.

627
00:34:44,550 --> 00:34:46,240
你改主意了吗  弗兰克
Are you changing your mind on this, Frank?

628
00:34:46,570 --> 00:34:50,590
我只是觉得  您该按自己的心意决定
I just think it's important that you do what you think is best.

629
00:34:51,100 --> 00:34:53,460
美国人民选您当总统
The American people voted you president.

630
00:34:53,460 --> 00:34:55,990
不是我  也不是雷蒙德·塔斯克
Not me. Not Raymond Tusk.

631
00:34:58,060 --> 00:34:59,330
我决定了再告诉你
I'll let you know what I decide.

632
00:34:59,340 --> 00:35:00,140
谢谢  总统先生
Thank you, sir.

633
00:35:06,570 --> 00:35:08,170
你觉得安德伍德选的是她吗
You think she's Underwood's choice?

634
00:35:09,000 --> 00:35:11,160
他没直说  所以有可能
He deflected, so it's possible.

635
00:35:18,020 --> 00:35:18,940
你和我
You and I,

636
00:35:20,180 --> 00:35:21,980
我们得合作  韦斯
we need to work together on this, Wes.

637
00:35:22,650 --> 00:35:24,100
否则我们俩都得完蛋
Before we both get screwed.

638
00:35:24,100 --> 00:35:25,030
我同意
I agree.

639
00:35:28,470 --> 00:35:30,000
我们中一个人退出
One of us drops out,

640
00:35:30,860 --> 00:35:32,280
支持另一个人
throws support to the other.

641
00:35:33,510 --> 00:35:35,490
这就能削弱她的支持力量
That'll dwarf any following she has.

642
00:35:36,130 --> 00:35:38,490
你想让我退出吗
You want me to drop out.

643
00:35:38,540 --> 00:35:41,000
我一定任命你做众议院拨款委员会主席
I'll make sure you get my chairmanship on appropriations.

644
00:35:44,520 --> 00:35:48,680
你至多能任命我做纪律委员会主席  这没人稀罕
All you can offer me is, uh, Ethics, which nobody wants.

645
00:35:52,180 --> 00:35:53,800
我们把事定下来吧  韦斯
Let's put this to bed, Wes.

646
00:35:58,170 --> 00:35:59,820
韦伯肯定跟他谈了协议
Webb must have offered him a deal.

647
00:35:59,940 --> 00:36:01,380
那我们就提出更好的条件
Then we have to offer a better one.

648
00:36:01,380 --> 00:36:04,160
我猜是拨款委员会  我给不了更好的
I'm guessing appropriations. There's no way I can top that.

649
00:36:04,160 --> 00:36:05,830
除非是财政委员会
Except for ways and means.

650
00:36:06,760 --> 00:36:11,550
我不能让你把职位给巴克沃特这样的混蛋
I -- I won't let you give your chair to an ass like Buchwalter.

651
00:36:11,550 --> 00:36:12,380
如果你是党鞭
If you're the Whip,

652
00:36:12,380 --> 00:36:14,640
你地位比他  和其他主席都高
you outrank him and every other chairman.

653
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:15,400
去他的委员会
Screw committees.

654
00:36:15,400 --> 00:36:17,510
我能直接跟议长交流
I'll have a direct line to the speaker.

655
00:36:18,100 --> 00:36:19,940
别固执了  杰姬
Don't be stubborn, Jackie.

656
00:36:20,600 --> 00:36:21,780
你觉得他会接受吗
You think he'd take it?

657
00:36:21,800 --> 00:36:23,810
他连韦伯的条件都愿意接受
He was willing to take a deal from Webb.

658
00:36:23,810 --> 00:36:26,130
但你是他最讨厌的人
But you're the only person he hates more.

659
00:36:26,290 --> 00:36:29,780
他很蛮人  但不是傻子
He's a brute. But he's not an idiot.

660
00:36:38,340 --> 00:36:40,530
我知道你不是出于忠诚而拒绝
Well, I know you're not refusing out of loyalty.

661
00:36:40,530 --> 00:36:41,400
没错
True.

662
00:36:42,260 --> 00:36:44,320
所以是泰德的缘故
So it's because of Ted.

663
00:36:48,390 --> 00:36:51,070
你觉得自己很厉害  对吧
You think you are hot shit, don't you?

664
00:36:52,400 --> 00:36:56,070
我们能放下架子  像成年人那样谈正经事吗
Can we set egos aside and talk business like the adults we are?

665
00:36:58,630 --> 00:37:00,420
我想要的不只是财政委员会主席之位
I want more than ways and means.

666
00:37:00,420 --> 00:37:01,110
说吧
Tell me.

667
00:37:01,780 --> 00:37:05,050
我要哈维梅耶走人  不只是退休
I want Havemeyer gone. Not just retired....

668
00:37:10,710 --> 00:37:12,100
让他从政坛消失
Politically dead.

669
00:37:13,160 --> 00:37:14,940
竞选是12年前的事了
That race was 12 years ago.

670
00:37:14,940 --> 00:37:16,960
不是他  我也能当12年参议员了
That was 12 years I could have been in the Senate.

671
00:37:18,120 --> 00:37:21,320
你就想报复  真的吗
Revenge? Really?

672
00:37:22,690 --> 00:37:24,010
不是报复
Not revenge.

673
00:37:26,330 --> 00:37:27,520
是报应
Equity.

674
00:37:30,020 --> 00:37:31,240
那你准备怎么办
Well, what are you gonna do?

675
00:37:31,240 --> 00:37:32,500
巴克沃特不会让步的
Buchwalter won't budge.

676
00:37:33,840 --> 00:37:37,770
我这一生最鄙视小气之人
You know, there's nothing I despise more in life than pettiness.

677
00:37:37,890 --> 00:37:40,380
我可以去找韦伯  但我给不了他什么
I could approach Webb, but I don't have enough to offer him.

678
00:37:40,380 --> 00:37:43,120
他不会退选的  他自尊心太强
Ah, he'd never drop out. Too much pride.

679
00:37:44,400 --> 00:37:45,760
我不知道该怎么办
I'm not sure what to do.

680
00:37:46,140 --> 00:37:49,390
这是泰德的档案  他有个私生女
This is my file on Ted. An illegitimate daughter.

681
00:37:49,390 --> 00:37:50,870
和保姆生的
The nanny, of course.

682
00:37:50,870 --> 00:37:53,680
她叫艾米莉·罗德里格斯  19岁了
Her name is Emily Rodriguez. 19.

683
00:37:53,830 --> 00:37:54,820
患脑中风
Cerebral palsy.

684
00:37:54,820 --> 00:37:55,860
我知道艾米莉的事
I know about Emily.

685
00:37:59,860 --> 00:38:01,420
那我们还在这里讨论什么
Well, then why are we having this conversation?

686
00:38:01,420 --> 00:38:02,590
这说来话长
It's complicated.

687
00:38:02,710 --> 00:38:05,350
私生女  我没看出有什么复杂的
The daughter? It's very black and white to me.

688
00:38:06,630 --> 00:38:08,530
我跟泰德是一辈子的交情
I've known Ted since I was born.

689
00:38:08,530 --> 00:38:10,100
他跟我父亲是好友
He and my father were very close.

690
00:38:10,100 --> 00:38:10,960
是的  我知道
Yeah, I'm aware.

691
00:38:10,960 --> 00:38:12,500
他一直都对我关照有加
He's always looked out for me.

692
00:38:12,890 --> 00:38:15,810
他把我送进西点军校  资助我第一次竞选
He got me into West Point. He funded my first race.

693
00:38:15,810 --> 00:38:17,800
我喜欢泰德  他一直都很有团队精神
I like Ted. He's always been a team player.

694
00:38:17,800 --> 00:38:19,820
很不幸  他拥有这样的秘密
It's unfortunate he has this secret.

695
00:38:19,820 --> 00:38:21,990
这是个错误  他一直都很后悔
It was a mistake. One he's always regretted.

696
00:38:22,180 --> 00:38:24,160
她出生之后  他让我去探望她
After she was born he asked me to check in on her,

697
00:38:24,160 --> 00:38:27,050
因为他自己做不到  而他信任我
because he couldn't. Because he trusted me.

698
00:38:28,960 --> 00:38:30,240
我懂了
I see.

699
00:38:31,030 --> 00:38:34,110
你来这里的时候就知道你该做什么
You came in here knowing what you had to do,

700
00:38:34,110 --> 00:38:37,220
但还是希望我能变个戏法  你就不用那么做了
hoping I would pull a rabbit out of a hat so you wouldn't have to.

701
00:38:37,220 --> 00:38:38,660
我认识这姑娘
I know the girl.

702
00:38:40,090 --> 00:38:42,330
我认识她母亲  她们不该经受那种事
I know her mother. These people don't deserve this.

703
00:38:42,330 --> 00:38:43,830
我该支的招都支了
I've given you all I can.

704
00:38:43,830 --> 00:38:45,440
你要如何决定是你自己的事
Whatever you decide is your prerogative.

705
00:38:45,440 --> 00:38:47,430
但也许我错看了你
But maybe I misjudged you.

706
00:38:49,020 --> 00:38:50,220
泰德对我来说就像家人一样
Ted is family to me.

707
00:38:50,220 --> 00:38:52,830
用来取代亲生女儿的养女
An adopted daughter in lieu of a real one.

708
00:38:53,910 --> 00:38:55,480
先生  国务卿来了
Sir, the secretary is here.

709
00:38:55,480 --> 00:38:58,050
谢谢  让她进来  你下去吧
Thank you. Send her in. Excuse us.

710
00:39:09,650 --> 00:39:10,330
很好
It's good.

711
00:39:10,330 --> 00:39:11,360
是不是太长了
Not too long?

712
00:39:11,370 --> 00:39:12,620
有一点  但也还好
A little bit, but not much.

713
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:16,150
这部分  第三段
This part, three paragraphs in.

714
00:39:16,940 --> 00:39:18,230
关于电话公司吗
Oh, about the phone companies?

715
00:39:18,230 --> 00:39:18,950
多跟我讲讲
Tell me more.

716
00:39:18,950 --> 00:39:21,530
这是国土安全部的主要担忧之一
It's one of Homeland Security's major concerns.

717
00:39:21,530 --> 00:39:24,130
网络攻击会渗透电话运营商
That the cyber attacks might infiltrate phone carriers,

718
00:39:24,140 --> 00:39:26,290
得到数百万人的数据记录
get access to millions of people's data history.

719
